Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.96,0:00:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep\NThe music is
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.76,0:00:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,so incredible. I can't function on its\Nown.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.07,0:00:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Beauty just wipes you out. You have to\Navoid beauty if you're going to stay in
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.52,0:00:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the world.\NI try to avoid beauty as much as I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.96,0:01:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I notice how beautiful my fingers\Nare.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.80,0:01:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true. Uh that calibrates at 750.\NExquisite beauty takes you beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.76,0:01:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,what the nervous system can handle.\NSo I said in the book I'm finishing now
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.36,0:01:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,or the one I just finished, I don't\Nremember which,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.60,0:01:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that when people get to a certain level\Nof consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.52,0:01:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,there is a tendency to leave the world\Nbecause one gets sort of removed by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.79,0:01:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh\Nyou can see how hard it is to function
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.88,0:01:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,at 7:50,\Nto be in the condition that that music
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.92,0:01:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,takes you to\Nand take the subway and get to work on
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.43,0:02:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,time,\Nwould feel a little difficult. So the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.32,0:02:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,tendency is to withdraw\Nfrom the world
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.36,0:02:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and rebalance. uh if it's possible to\Nrebalance
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.28,0:02:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and to see\Nwhat one's remaining capacities may be.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.08,0:02:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NToday we're going to be talking about u
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.36,0:02:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,karma, a subject which is familiar to\Nthose of an eastern background and not
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.23,0:02:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,all that familiar to people with a\Nwestern background.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.95,0:02:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,However, you know, familiar to uh\Nspiritual students
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.80,0:03:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and um so I thought I would uh focus\Ntoday on its implications, its real
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.92,0:03:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,significance,\Num
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.76,0:03:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,its complexity and at the same time\Nsimplicity
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.72,0:03:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and um what it really means.\NWe said that um
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.31,0:03:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the\Nthe entire
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.15,0:03:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,universe is one karmic unity.\NThere is one all-encompassing
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.48,0:03:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic totality to the allness of all of\Ncreation
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.44,0:03:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in which everything is in from moment to\Nmoment incredible and perfect balance
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.15,0:04:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,with everything else.\Nharmonic perfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.15,0:04:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Part of that\Nperfection, harmonic perfection,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.08,0:04:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is\Nwhat appears to be chaotic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.32,0:04:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And that which seems to be chaotic and\Nrule against the harmonic balance of the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.07,0:04:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,universe\Nis only so because of it being perceived
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.72,0:04:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in that way.\NThat harmony includes the capacity.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.40,0:05:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You might say the quantum potentiality\Nto suddenly become its opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.00,0:05:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,gentle, gentle children, listen to me,\NI'll kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.52,0:05:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,People say, "Where did that come from?"\NAdolf Hitler had been loud and bang,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.16,0:05:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,man. And we were praying and singing and\Nenjoying the incense and all of a sudden
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.03,0:05:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,a bomb came out of someplace. How can\Nthat be? Doesn't that disprove the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.16,0:05:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,existence of God?\NWell,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.28,0:05:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,God's hard to get rid of.\NGod just won the vote
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.63,0:05:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,back into existence again. I was so\Nrelieved. I thought they were going to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.91,0:05:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,vote God out of existence, out of the\Nmoney, out of the constitution.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.72,0:05:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They're going to take it and God we\Ntrust and eliminate it. Boy, I was
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.12,0:06:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,scared.\NBut God made it just made it through by
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.96,0:06:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,three votes or something or five volts.\NI understand there were five idiots that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.96,0:06:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,voted against it.\NRemember uh what was her name? Maline
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.31,0:06:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Murray O'Hare.\NSpeaking of karma,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.24,0:06:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember this guy on TV trying to\Nunite God from every from our society.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.16,0:06:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought, Jesus, doesn't he ever\Nread the story of me? Well, you never
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.36,0:06:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,heard of karma.\NKarma is uh interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.24,0:06:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh boy, I'm back in the intellect again.\NThank you. Lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.72,0:06:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,back into reason and logic. That was\Nscary.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.36,0:07:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes I think I'm going to\Ndisappear. I was talking to my friend
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.68,0:07:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,here this morning. I said, "Are you\Ngetting smaller?" You get He seems to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.56,0:07:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,getting smaller every time I see him.\NMy clothes keep getting bigger and as
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.80,0:07:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,time goes on, you get smaller and\Nsmaller. Pretty soon you you're looking
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.47,0:07:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,up to see yourself in the mirror.\NEventually, you disappear, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.84,0:07:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the karma\Nkarma is really an incredibly great
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.59,0:07:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,story. You can also skip it all\Ntogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.52,0:07:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,At any one instant, you can just\Ncompletely and totally surrender all
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.84,0:07:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that you think you are to God. And um\Nof course that could be a karmically
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.44,0:07:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,determined event.\NWhat is the significance of karma? In in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.24,0:08:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,some instances, it's a profound\Nsignificance. It also makes
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.56,0:08:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,has has the capacity to light up areas\Nof your own life. so that they make
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.56,0:08:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,sense.\NWithout understanding karma
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.36,0:08:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,as is done in the west,\Nit leaves one with really one only one
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.03,0:08:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,tool to approach God and that's faith.\NBecause nothing in life makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.00,0:08:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are some children born crippled and\Nblind? Born with AIDS, born from cocaine
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.59,0:08:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,addicted mothers with brain damage.\NWe noted in earlier lectures that at the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.88,0:08:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,moment of birth, everybody already has a\Ncalibrated level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.12,0:08:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,At the moment of birth,\Ninstantly you enter this domain at a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.44,0:08:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated level of consciousness.\NNow we could explain physical
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.27,0:09:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,differences genetically. We could say,\Nwell, that genetic pot pour
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.72,0:09:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,um the game of chance of genes and\Nsperms and all that stuff
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.32,0:09:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,would explain why\Nthis child is crippled, this child is
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.64,0:09:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,blind, this child is deaf, and this\Nchild is a genius, and this child writes
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.39,0:09:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,symphonies at age four.\NThat would be the mechanistic
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.36,0:09:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,reductionistic\Nuh scientific explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.32,0:09:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just genetic chance,\Ncombinations and permutations of all
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.36,0:09:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,those genes and chromosomes.\NAnd so that would be fine
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.00,0:09:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,except that when we calibrate their\Nlevels of consciousness, we find that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.48,0:09:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the calibrated level of consciousness is\Ncompletely different. That is not
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.04,0:09:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,genetically determined. It's not\Ndetermined by chromosomes. In fact, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.51,0:10:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the other way around. Because of karmic\Ninheritance,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.16,0:10:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,one automatically comes into certain\Ngenetic and chromosomeal
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.12,0:10:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,uh patterns which then become the\Nmechanism by which that karmic
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.27,0:10:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,propensity expresses itself.\NWhat we see in the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.51,0:10:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,visible domain,\Nthe discernable domain is consequences
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.95,0:10:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and not causes.\NThe fastest spiritual advance is to jump
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.00,0:10:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond the mind's belief in causality.\NThere is no causality anywhere in this
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.00,0:10:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,domain. There's nothing causing\Nanything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.07,0:10:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All is becoming that which it is out of\Nits own karmic potentiality and
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.68,0:10:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,fulfillment. Because creation\Nreveals itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.27,0:10:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And as it reveals itself, perception\Nsees it as progressive and calls it
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.92,0:11:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution. Yeah.\NSo from the moment of birth there is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.68,0:11:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,already\Nlet's say a quality of karma that we can
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.16,0:11:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate as a level of consciousness.\NWe use this little pattern here
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.68,0:11:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,just sort of like a homing base, you\Nknow, so I remember where I am here in
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.80,0:11:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the world. Oh, yes.\NWell, most of the people I'm talking
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.51,0:11:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,about aren't even on here.\NThey didn't make it that far.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.95,0:11:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So this\Ndomain seems to be purgatorial in in its
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.76,0:11:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,qualities.\NLet's ask if we got permission to ask
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.88,0:12:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that. We have permission to ask that\Nhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.72,0:12:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This is um\Num a um a purgatorial type domain that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.76,0:12:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in which\Nuh all opportunities exist both high and
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.24,0:12:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,low.\NOne can rise or fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.80,0:12:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,One gets a chance to undo the negative\Nkarma and acquire positive karma. All
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.20,0:12:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,right? So this is a formative domain\Npurgatorial.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.68,0:12:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You can tell it's purgatorial because it\Ngoes from the very ugliest and worst and
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.04,0:12:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,most horrific\Nto the most uh divine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.76,0:12:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The slums of some of the poorest\Ncountries in the world where I've been.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.60,0:12:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The slums are unbelievable.\NTo somebody who've grown up in the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.44,0:13:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,western world in America,\Nto walk through those slums and see the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.07,0:13:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,style of life is like shocking. You\Ndon't even believe it. It's not even
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.95,0:13:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,possible\Nthat that which calls itself human could
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.63,0:13:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,survive in these conditions.\Neating bugs,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.76,0:13:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,um bitten by rats,\Nuh using his building materials,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.63,0:13:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,pieces of scrap and cardboard all pasted\Ntogether
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.36,0:13:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,outside of uh what's it\Ncapital of Brazil?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.63,0:13:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Rio di Janeiro.\NWell, anyway, not Brasilia, but uh the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.95,0:13:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,old city was on the side of the mountain\Nthere. They call them, I forget the name
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.48,0:13:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of the world, the words, but uh they\Nlive in pieces of cardboard boxes and uh
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.16,0:13:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe a family of 12 lives on there and\Nthey take turns sleeping in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.68,0:14:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, anyway, it's incredible. And\Neverybody begs for a living.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.24,0:14:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The biggest mistake is to give a begging\Nchild a penny.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.88,0:14:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Then they're then over you like a swarm\Nof army ants
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.60,0:14:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and you realize that you're not going to\Nbe able to hold back this flood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.56,0:14:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You can hand out money to the children\Ncoming up to you and it's not going to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.72,0:14:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,alter anything because there's floods of\Nthem. As you go out handfuls of pennies,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.51,0:14:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,more and more and more come and more and\Nmore and more come. They would come from
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.00,0:14:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,miles and miles and miles\Nand you see that it's not going to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.24,0:14:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,change anything at all\Ntrying to change the circumstance
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.80,0:14:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because what you're seeing is is the\Neffect. You're seeing the effect. You're
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.76,0:14:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,not seeing the cause.\NCertain neighborhoods pull to them
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.80,0:14:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is negative. The broken\Nwindow theory in sociology.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.39,0:15:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The first broken factory window, if you\Ndon't repair it, brings graffiti. The
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.12,0:15:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,graffiti brings the crime. That brings\Nthe rape. That brings the robbery. That
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.24,0:15:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,brings the drugs. That brings the arson.\NThat brings the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.07,0:15:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The negative energy field then pulls to\Nit all that which is aligned with that
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.27,0:15:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,field.\NPeople say I don't believe in karma. I
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.72,0:15:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,don't want anybody to believe in karma\Nbecause what one is at any instant
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.12,0:15:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is the karmic conclusion of all that is\Npreceded.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.04,0:15:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You know we the main reason it's not\Nwell understood in the west is Jesus did
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.92,0:15:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,not get into it in any great depth. He\Nonly mentioned it briefly
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.16,0:16:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,as a subject. Uh\Nbut the teachings of Christianity
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.60,0:16:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,are\Nthat all actions
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.60,0:16:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,have a consequence,\Na spiritual consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.04,0:16:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,in in another domain that it has to do\Nwith the fact that every action then has
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.39,0:16:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,some kind of a registering in the soul.\NSome kind of aspect of the soul
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.00,0:16:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,registers\Nfor all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.75,0:16:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,every action and decision and this will\Ndetermine your fate in later
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.88,0:16:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,other dimensions.\NHeavens, hells and purgatories
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.80,0:16:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,are pretty much accepted by all the\Nworld's religions as a reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.36,0:16:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes people resist karma because\Nthey have it cons confused with
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.44,0:17:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,reincarnation. They are two different\Nthings. Reincarnation is one thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.16,0:17:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,karma is another.\NAll religions teach karma but they don't
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.07,0:17:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,use that term. That is what a Sanskrit\Nterm karma I suppose. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.31,0:17:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't use the terminology\Nbecause life seems unfair to yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.07,0:17:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and to others. As you look around\Nthere's a bitterness towards God and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.88,0:17:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually even a hatred of God\Ncomes out of the lack of karma
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.48,0:17:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding karma. Therefore, I think\Nit's beneficial
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.24,0:17:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,beneficial to one's faith and\Nunderstanding
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.32,0:17:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand that what you see are\Nconsequences
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.16,0:17:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,consequences consequences\Nof things that have been brought over
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.44,0:17:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,brought in to one's life over long\Nexpanses of time
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.44,0:18:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,with no understanding of karma. God then\Nappears unfair unfair.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.03,0:18:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is how does God allow this crippled\Nchild to be born? You hear that all the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.16,0:18:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,time.\NTherefore, I don't believe in God. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.72,0:18:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,failure to comprehend karma, I think,\Nleads to a lot of atheism and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.67,0:18:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,agnosticism\Nand even eventually rage and hatred of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.24,0:18:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,God\Nbecause it doesn't accept
