Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.96,0:22:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,100. You know\Nand his teachings were unpopular at the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.36,0:22:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,time\Nto put it mildly. Yeah. He was not
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.40,0:22:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly a popular teacher around town\Nand um to the powers that be. So I also
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.12,0:22:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,thought in the height of wisdom he just\Ndidn't bring it up as a specific topic
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.64,0:22:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,per se.\NHe he said it that all your actions will
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.32,0:23:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,have consequences in a later life.\NHe did mention once in Matthew something
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.28,0:23:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,about Isaiah has come back to us as John\Nthe Baptist in Matthew. That's the only
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.20,0:23:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the only quote making a direct\Nreference. Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.60,0:23:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,on such an advanced level of\Nconsciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.48,0:23:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's obvious that what you are\Nthat the ego and your karma and that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.79,0:23:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,which you are are all one the same\Nthing. You don't have to worry about
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.79,0:23:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,karma. Just work on what your problems\Nare in the present because they are the
