Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.00,0:27:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,thankful for them because you say well\Nif I was an so in past lifetimes and
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.76,0:27:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,cruel and selfish and\Nbeat my wife every day like they do in
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.24,0:27:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,other parts of the world. It's your duty\Nto beat your wife every day in certain
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.55,0:27:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,parts of the world. Maybe they have to\Ncome back and get beaten because they
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.67,0:27:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,fail to beat their wife every day. And\Nso it puts it into proportion. So some
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.72,0:27:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding of karma then gets you out\Nof self-pity, resentment, hatred, hatred
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.03,0:27:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of God,\Ncursing God for being unfair.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.79,0:27:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and putting you here with whatever\Nlimitations you have. And everyone has
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.96,0:27:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,limitations\Nbecause all of creation is one karmic
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.27,0:28:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,unity.\NThen we represent not only personal
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.24,0:28:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,karma but we represent the karmic\Npattern the karmic the evolution of
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.08,0:28:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness\Non this planet
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.39,0:28:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,uh and to where it has evolved in the\Nevolution of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.76,0:28:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're stuck with the karma of mankind\Nitself.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.60,0:28:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Homo sapienism,\Na bad disease. Homo sapienism
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.76,0:28:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,which can give you everything.\NArthritis, blindness, stiffness,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.20,0:28:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,convulsions,\Na lot goes with it. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.84,0:28:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Having to work for a living. Yeah.\NAnd all those unfairnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.96,0:28:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay to talk about the daisies in\Nthe field. Neither do they labor to. It
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.60,0:28:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,wasn't a human being out there in the\Nfield. They wouldn't be just sitting
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.32,0:28:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,there\Nlooking beautiful waving in the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.12,0:29:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd be going to work.\NGet a shovel, Daisy. And let's see how
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.60,0:29:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,good you think about it.\NFred Fred was over at our house for the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.12,0:29:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,weekend and and was shoveling dirt. You\Nsee,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.27,0:29:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,she was a daisy. He wouldn't have to\Nshovel dirt. You could just sit there
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.00,0:29:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and look pretty.\Nhelped us out with a greenhouse which
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.00,0:29:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,had fallen down. Its karmic propensity\Nwas to decay over time with dry rot.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.15,0:29:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,An understanding of karma then is\Nimportant to look at it that you didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.12,0:29:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,just arrive spontaneously out of nowhere\Nas you are at this moment. that somehow
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.72,0:29:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the evolution of consciousness.\NNow life and consciousness are one and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.39,0:29:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the same.\NUm we went back into
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.67,0:30:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,um\Nprior to the universe this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.08,0:30:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Susan and I I said let's go back\Npriority. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.15,0:30:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We got out of the man unmanifest comes\Nthe manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.64,0:30:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the unmanifest comes the\Nmanifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.12,0:30:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But consciousness, consciousness and\Nlife are one and the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.39,0:30:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And they don't appear until\Nexistence,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.03,0:30:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,until the manifest expresses itself as\Nexistence.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.79,0:30:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That which has no existence is beyond\Nconsciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.72,0:30:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NOut of the unmanifest arises the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.03,0:30:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,manifest. Resist. The manifest is the\Nvoid of life or consciousness. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.36,0:30:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the manifest arises existence.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.60,0:31:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Innate to existence is consciousness.\NAnd consciousness and life are one and
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.44,0:31:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the same.\NWow.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.00,0:31:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's enough before breakfast.\Nto know that consciousness and life
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.03,0:31:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,are cannot be extinguished. H let's see\Nif that's so
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.91,0:31:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,life cannot be extinguished. Resist.\NConsciousness cannot be extinguished.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.60,0:31:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NWow. What does that mean? That means
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.39,0:31:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,death is impossible.\NThat which has life has life eternally.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.48,0:31:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is conscious.\NYou can swat the fly, but you can't kill
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.15,0:31:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,its life energy because it flits around\Nin the astral and comes right back as
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.32,0:32:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,another fly.\NYou can't extinguish life or
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.27,0:32:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness. When I was a kid, it was\Nokay to have mercury. My father would
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.36,0:32:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,bring home mercury\Nwhich they took out a filling stations
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.12,0:32:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,or something and and we had a wonderful\Ncollection of mercury. Bum b was real
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.36,0:32:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,heavy go. Now it' be illegal I guess\Nbecause mercury vapor poisoning would
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.24,0:32:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,send everybody into paranoid fits and\Nyou'd have the EPA knocking at your
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.15,0:32:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,door. But in those days we lived in a\Nmore simple world of ignorance. So we
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.20,0:32:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,would put it in a\Nwe put it in a bowl. Well, to amuse me,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.39,0:32:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,my father would pour some mercury in\Nthis thing and I of course try to pick
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.84,0:32:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it up. You know, maybe for then I try\Nand pick up the mercury and it would
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.84,0:32:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,just go that way. You pick up that one,\Nit would go that way. No matter what you
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.27,0:32:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,did, you can't pick up the mercury. It\Njust moves around someplace else.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.03,0:32:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is the way life then is. Cannot be\Nextinguished.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.76,0:33:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we have to give up fearing death\Nbecause it's it's not going to be an
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.96,0:33:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,escape hatch. No, you're not going to\Nget out of the deal with death.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.84,0:33:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody grieves death and oh, I fear\Ndeath. Come on. I know. On the other
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.15,0:33:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,side of your consciousness,\Nit's your big cop out.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.44,0:33:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'll die and get away from it all.\NWell, it should be that easy, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.12,0:33:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it seems the karmic propensities\Nthen prevail
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.08,0:33:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in and out weaving through.\NIt could be an infinite number of
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.72,0:33:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,lifetimes.\NIt can be an infinite number of human
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.72,0:33:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,lifetimes.\NI never asked that before.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.51,0:33:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's possible to have an infinite number\Nof human lifetime resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.12,0:33:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nain't that neat?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.24,0:34:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you never want to go to heaven.\NYou never want to go to hell. You just
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.44,0:34:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,want to go to work every day,\N>> propagate, have sex,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.07,0:34:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,eat up a storm. You can keep doing it.\NWow,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.72,0:34:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,what a relief.\NOh, mint chocolate chip ice cream. I do
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.15,0:34:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,not have to leave thee.\NI'll get old, toddler over, come back as
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.52,0:34:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,another little kid, and have my\Nchocolate chip and ice cream again. No
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.80,0:34:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,end. Endless.\NYou never have to return to God. Is that
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.91,0:34:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,a fact?\NYou never have to return to God and
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.59,0:34:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,resist. You never have to become\Nenlightened. Resist. You can just keep
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.72,0:34:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,going like this forever.\N>> Whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.56,0:35:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So man, some people that's going to be\Nrelief
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.83,0:35:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,other people\Nit means unless you do some kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.32,0:35:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,progressive spiritual work you're going\Nto keep reincarnating as a physical as a
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.52,0:35:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,human being. Um that's soul resist you\Nyou have choice to reincarnate resist
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.04,0:35:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,from the astral domains resist. So being\Nhere is a choice. A choice because it's
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.04,0:35:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,a place to evolve. Resist.\NThe reason um
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.20,0:35:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,we have permission to ask about what I'm\Nthinking about resist
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.28,0:35:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,um\Nthat which is is most um
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.11,0:35:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,there are domains where\Num people go who refu refuse God resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.16,0:35:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't have to go to God in a\Nnumber of ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.16,0:35:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not necessary. You can just keep\Nrecycling.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.96,0:36:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You can keep recycling until inspiration\Ncomes to move on ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.88,0:36:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the Buddha apparently didn't like\Nphysical reincarnations cuz he didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.40,0:36:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,speak too highly of it.\NHe said, "Unless you become enlightened,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.80,0:36:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you're you're going to have to get re\Nrefysicalized periodically or
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.16,0:36:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,reincarnate."\NUm,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.48,0:36:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course he was looking at the\Ndownside of human life. He was looking
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.40,0:36:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,at\Nold age, sorrow, poverty, and death.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.96,0:36:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that those things he thought were\Ninevitable, inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.83,0:36:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And that the way beyond it was to\Ntranscend karma
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.04,0:36:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,by becoming enlightened, meaning to\Ntranscend one's identification with the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.83,0:36:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,ego,\Nits origin, its function, and its
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.35,0:37:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,structure.\NAnd to realize the self, to realize
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.04,0:37:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,one's Buddha nature.\NChristianity does does not emphasize
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.11,0:37:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightenment at all.\NThere is in
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.92,0:37:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Catholicism\Na condition or one
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.20,0:37:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot the formal ecclesiastic name\Nfor it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.80,0:37:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It signifies a high level of\Nconsciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.40,0:37:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,as a lifestyle.\NChristianity recognizes saintthood
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.07,0:37:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and generally is talking about the 500s,\Nhigh 500s
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.07,0:37:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,like Father Peel\Nat 590, the pope at 570. the Pope to me
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.11,0:37:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is saying like\Num
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.64,0:38:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's just my perception. I can\Ntell by the way he walks.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.52,0:38:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He's gotten higher as he got older. So\Nit gets you slow down as the level of
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.59,0:38:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness goes up.\NYou have to forcibly stay out of that
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.72,0:38:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,certain level of consciousness or it's\Nnot possible to function very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.59,0:38:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So I see he sort of fights with it.\NTherefore, whatever goes on in our life
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.48,0:38:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,currently is really the consequence of\Nthe totality of all that has gone before
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.52,0:38:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,as it is expressing itself under current\Nconditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.52,0:38:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not causing the current conditions.\NIt's expressing itself in this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.68,0:38:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It has the potentiality to express\Nitself and under these conditions that
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.44,0:39:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality will express itself this\Nway and under these conditions that
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.00,0:39:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality will express itself this\Nway.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.59,0:39:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So nothing is\Nnothing is uh a rigid causality an
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.00,0:39:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,inflexible causality.\NOn the contrary, closer to truth is the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.48,0:39:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,whole concept of quantum potentiality\Nin which the prior what has gone before
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.59,0:39:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is influencing not just specifically the\Ncontent of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.72,0:39:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,it's\Ninfluencing the whole context.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.83,0:39:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So the whole context then is what\Nincreases
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.72,0:39:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the likelihood of certain potentialities\Nuh coming into expression
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.20,0:39:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,in spiritual work. We in the beginning\Nfocus on
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.32,0:39:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,uh content of consciousness.\NHow could I have been so mean to my
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.96,0:40:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,stepmother? How could I have been so\Nthis and that to my mother-in-law? And
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.24,0:40:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you feel guilty how you were selfish and\Nstole your sister's cookie the last
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.44,0:40:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,cookie on her birthday. You've been\Nreally guilty about that for 45 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.40,0:40:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And that she was some little dinky thing\Nway back there. And you somehow you
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.76,0:40:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,can't get it out of your head.\NYou took the last cookie from your on
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.56,0:40:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,your sister's birthday.\NOh, that selfishness, that greediness,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.28,0:40:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that horribleness.\NYou hate yourself for it. It's horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.07,0:40:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,50 years later, you're still at it.\NProbably on death's door, you're going
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.32,0:40:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to say, "God, I I stole my sister's\Ncookie. Please
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.44,0:40:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,let me off the hook."\NGuilt just looks for uh something to
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.48,0:40:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,anchor itself into. It isn't just the\Nguilt about your sister's cookie. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.24,0:41:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,all the accumulated guilt\Nuh about everything throughout all of
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.96,0:41:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,lifetimes anchoring itself into this\Nparticular expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.48,0:41:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Some comprehension of the nature of\Nkarma and maybe how it came about in
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.80,0:41:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,your own lifetime can facilitate certain\Ndifficult things to transcend. Make them
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.07,0:41:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,easier.\NMake them easier to transcend. here.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.16,0:41:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I've shared some some things from other\Nlifetimes with you, you know, and we've
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.04,0:41:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,had sort of fun with it. We have fun\Nwith it because now in this time I can
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.52,0:41:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,look back and now I feel light about it.\NI'm sure at the time I didn't feel all
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.96,0:41:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that light about it.\NIt's because we recontextualize it. So
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.88,0:41:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes if you're stuck in something,\Nyou can ask, is this a karmic
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.28,0:41:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,propensity? Yeah. Uh has this was this a\Nbad? Usually what you look for is the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.59,0:42:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,opposite. You you look for the opposite.\NWhat's happening to you? You ask,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.59,0:42:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,was that what I did to others in my past\Nlife? And now I see what it's like. And
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.11,0:42:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the only way, so one of the ways mind\Nundoes its guilt is to undo it by living
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.11,0:42:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it through and living living the side of\Nthe victim. So in the prior lifetime you
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.56,0:42:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,where you were the perpetrator, you now\Nhave the responsibility in this lifetime
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.76,0:42:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to undo that either by good works\Num or by experiencing it out and um
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.48,0:42:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,forgiving everything and everyone\Nincluding yourself. So the tool that
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.16,0:42:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,helps you through all of this is first\Nof all the comprehension does make many
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.72,0:42:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,things easier to accept\Nthat if you can go back with kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.11,0:42:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and saying such and in some lifetime did\NI do such and such or did such and such
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.56,0:43:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,thing happen\Nand then you can get sort of an aha well
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.72,0:43:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess it's I guess it makes sense then\Nand early in life I never heard of karma
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.07,0:43:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But I would always say, you know, I must\Nhave done something something to
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.04,0:43:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody in some lifetime to deserve\Nthat. You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.92,0:43:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It just sort of made sense that\Notherwise there would be no explanation
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.92,0:43:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,about for it except that God is\Narbitrary anatist.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.64,0:43:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many atheists in the world and\Nuh they're not all stupid. You know,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.20,0:43:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,many of them are quite brilliant.\NAnd when they look at the world through
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.04,0:43:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian paradigm of reality,\Num the idea that there's an infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.28,0:43:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,benevolent God who is not different than\Nlove is idiotic.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.48,0:43:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand? Logic, reason at a\Ncertain point will not take you to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.92,0:44:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll take you to atheism.\NAt one one level of consciousness, if
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.40,0:44:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not an atheist, I think you're\Nstupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.76,0:44:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a devout atheist for years and I\Nlooked at anybody who believed that God
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.35,0:44:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is an absolute idiot.\NYou look at the disaster of mankind and
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.24,0:44:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,say\NGod is the source of all this
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.04,0:44:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or you can keep him.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.00,0:44:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that was when I held God as the source\Nno the cause
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.92,0:44:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of the human karmic dilemma.\NWhat we see then as human tragedy is the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.83,0:44:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,effect of the ego\Nuncaused by God. So
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.16,0:45:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it's as though\Nthe capacity for existence and life and
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.68,0:45:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness is a given and then what\Nis done with it becomes one's own karmic
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.88,0:45:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,responsibility\Nthe consequences of which we see
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.72,0:45:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,collectively as society. Huh?\NBut when I became an atheist, it was
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.96,0:45:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,because the totality of the suffering of\Nall of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.40,0:45:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,opened up as a revelation. It was\Nstaggering.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.72,0:45:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a devout religionist\Nat the time and
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.92,0:45:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,scrupulous in fact scrupulous. And I\Ntold you I used to dread Saturday
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.31,0:45:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,afternoon. you went to confession that\Nyou wouldn't sin someplace before you
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.52,0:45:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,went to church on Sunday morning and had\Ncommunion.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.80,0:45:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I was out in the woods and\Nsuddenly the totality of the suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.35,0:45:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of all mankind throughout all of time\Nopened up in the most staggering
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.00,0:46:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,revelation\Non God on beyond the capacity of
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.07,0:46:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,ordinary human thinkingness to\Ncomprehend.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.16,0:46:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,staggering.\NIn that instant, I became an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.68,0:46:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,God went out that fast.\NCan't believe in a god that allows that
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.31,0:46:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,because when you look at the totality of\Nhuman suffering,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.07,0:46:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,one has to be of sizable dimension to\Neven glance at it. Just blows you away.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.92,0:46:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,In clinical practice, you know, you see\Nit peacemeal. You see it peace meal in
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.16,0:46:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the ER.\NIn war, you see it peace meal, but this
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.80,0:46:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,came on. Not peace meal, but all of it.\NSo, was I ever a devout atheist? And it
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.35,0:47:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,took Catholicism apart, Protestantism\Napart, the Reformation apart, the Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.28,0:47:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,idiotic.\NThomas Aquinus.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.83,0:47:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Good God, give me a break.\NI got straight A in theology.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.40,0:47:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And a Jesuit university. Straight A in\Nethics, straight A in logic, straight A
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.96,0:47:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in theology.\NUm because if you're going to be against
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.88,0:47:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,something, you better know a lot about\Nit.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.72,0:47:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Friday afternoon outside of\NMarquette University in the news bar,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.24,0:47:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, real our names on our mugs was take\Non all. I sat in the corner and I took
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.80,0:47:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,on all comers or the religionist and I\Nwould knock them out of the box one
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.00,0:47:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,after another.\NNever lost around. It's a fact. Never
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.76,0:48:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,lost around.\NAll right? Because
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.35,0:48:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,within the Newtonian paradigm of\Nreality,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.35,0:48:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, nothing about God is really\Nprovable. You have to go to the
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.04,0:48:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,nonlinear\Nwhere you're beyond causality. You're
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.72,0:48:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond logic.\NYou're beyond uh literalism
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.07,0:48:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and concrete.\NUm, and you get to greater dimensions.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.11,0:48:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Um\Nso it takes the greater dimensions to
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.20,0:48:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,heal the negativities that have arisen\Nout of karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.44,0:48:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The whatever one has inherited in one\Nway or another or come into because you
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.16,0:48:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,come into it just by being human. You\Nshare in human consciousness. The
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.92,0:48:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,totality of human consciousness\Nis something which dominates individual
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.59,0:49:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness.\NThe reason you can light up a whole
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.07,0:49:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,crowd of enthusiasts about something is\Nbecause that consciousness level is
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.00,0:49:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,available to the whole crowd.\NUh you know Fitler knew how to play that
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.59,0:49:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,like a you know he would play 10,000\Npeople shouting sigh at the same time
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.80,0:49:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was hypnotic you know.\NIf you weren't a Nazi in those years in
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.24,0:49:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Germany, you must have been brain dead\Nbecause
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.76,0:49:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it was persuasive. It was\Nall-encompassing. It was powerful. It
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.64,0:49:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,was patriotic. It was military. It was\Nit was grand.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.48,0:49:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that it was somewhat an error\Ndid not show up till later. But at the
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.28,0:49:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,time it was, you know, any normal kid\Nwould want to go to one of the boys
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.07,0:49:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,camps and learn how to become a member\Nof the Hitler Youth. You it' have to be
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.88,0:49:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,something wrong with you not to want to\Nbecause it was so prevailing in society.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.92,0:50:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see how these dominant levels of\Nconsciousness then have resonate in the
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.76,0:50:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,human condition because everybody in\Nthat crowd is a captive of the human
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.59,0:50:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,condition.\NThey're all born with the capacity for
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.96,0:50:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,loyalty, nationalism, enthusiasm,\Nmacho masculinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.96,0:50:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,militarism, all those things. You\Ninherit that as part of being a human.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.76,0:50:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nbut the worst thing you see go on in the
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.35,0:50:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,world historically or currently is\Nreally the consequence of being human.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.28,0:50:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,To be human being\Nto be to begin with a human being can't
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.76,0:50:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,tell truth from falsehood\Na walkling stumbling idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.44,0:50:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,How did we ever get this far? I don't\Nknow.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.20,0:50:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It boggles me that we even got here.\NCan you imagine a species that doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.16,0:50:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,know truth from falsehood? If you don't\Nknow truth from falsehood, that pretty
