Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.79,1:00:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Stealing a cookie\Nrequires death.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.44,1:00:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the kind of superhero I used to\Nhave. I mean, I know it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.52,1:00:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,God, I told you about the Jansen\Nswimsuit billboard. Good god.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.76,1:00:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,only death would.\NSo we want to amilarate our view of
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.11,1:00:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the world and our relationship with the\Nworld because the world is a projection
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.24,1:01:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of the ego. The savagery that you\Nhold against the world
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.83,1:01:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is nothing but a mirror that you hold\Nagainst yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.96,1:01:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you must have very severe things\Nthat you're holding against yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.07,1:01:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise,\Neveryone would become enlightened.
