Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.68,1:07:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,as knowledge in itself has a has the the\Nintrinsic action of a guru exist. The
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.16,1:07:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,truth itself. Okay. To to merely hear\Nthe truth already has
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.40,1:07:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the effect of the blessing of the guru\Nis this. Okay. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.68,1:07:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So to merely hear, to merely\Nknow certain things is already
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.64,1:07:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,elevating, already advances one's\Nconsciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.55,1:07:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,has a catalytic effect.\NSometimes just one little piece of
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.72,1:07:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,information like solves all kinds of\Nlittle things in the puzzle. They all
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.28,1:07:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,make sense. Sometimes karmic research\Ndoes that. comically search back and you
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.72,1:07:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,find some single event or collection of\Nevents or propensities in certain
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.68,1:08:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,lifetimes.\NUh and and now you see that over and
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.03,1:08:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,over again you're asked to go to\Ntranscend that to transcend that to
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.76,1:08:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,transcend that to value\Nmoney over life.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.07,1:08:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NIn the lifetime I'm thinking of I valued
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.71,1:08:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,money over life which is greed over\Nlife.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.19,1:08:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\Nto let people die out of greed. To to
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.23,1:08:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,value gain, greed, money, treasure\Nover the value of human life, to
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.31,1:08:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,sacrifice human life for money. So\Nthat's a pretty common one, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.19,1:08:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody who's lived before is likely\Nhave done that, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.60,1:08:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because human consciousness has\Nevolved from the animal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.60,1:09:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless you're a greedy animal, you\Nreally don't survive. How long does an
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.35,1:09:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,altruistic animal survive?\NHere, Hubert, you can have my bone.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.27,1:09:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And if there's any left, I'll have\Nwhat's left.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.31,1:09:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NWell, you get smaller and smaller and
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.88,1:09:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,finally you follow her.\NUh,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.52,1:09:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,so our first commitment is to be a good\Nanimal. A good animal, you have to have
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.48,1:09:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain gusto for life\Nand a certain love of life and
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.15,1:09:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,enthusiasm for life. You got to have the\Ncapacity to get in there and walk.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.96,1:09:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There's times when you got to do that.\NThat's the only spiritual thing you can
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.60,1:09:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,do.\NFeeble monks aren't worth a nickel.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.04,1:10:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm praying.\NGet off your knees, old man. Sweep the
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.15,1:10:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,floor. Don't you see all the crap around\Nhere?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.36,1:10:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\None of my missions was um
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.48,1:10:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,one of my secret ambitions I'll have to\Nlet go. It was to be a verger in a great
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.00,1:10:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,cathedral.\NCan you imagine? You know, you're the
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.64,1:10:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,janitor. You don't have to talk to\Nanybody, say anything to anybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.44,1:10:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,People are idiotic. You don't have to\Nlisten to their paddle.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.76,1:10:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You get to hear the choir practicing\NThursday nights, Wednesday nights. You
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.40,1:10:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,get to live around incense,\Nstained glass windows, incredible
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.48,1:10:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,sculpture, incredible beauty.\NIt's the way to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.44,1:10:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I think God is jealous of the\Nkeeps the job of janitor in the great
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.80,1:10:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,cathedral\Nfor his favorite ones.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.48,1:11:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If I'm going to have another lifetime,\NI'd like to be a verger and a great no
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.56,1:11:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,one\Ncuz then by then I'll have all kinds of
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.92,1:11:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,regulations.\Nfingerprint
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.40,1:11:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,fingerprint register and uh you know I\Nmean you'll have ver vger regs coming
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.15,1:11:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,out from the welfare department\Nso the day of the vir cathedral is over
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.60,1:11:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to see that's a oh I see what that is\Nthat's an attachment to a previous
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.08,1:11:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,lifetimehu\Nthank you
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.40,1:11:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,all right so that hankering which came\Nup this morning. The minute I hear that
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.80,1:11:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,music, it throws me into the ecstasy of\Nbeauty, you know, which is a very rapid
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.00,1:11:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,pathway to God.\NWhen you because to just immerse oneself
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.28,1:11:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in beauty,\Nthe oneness of beauty and God and the
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.52,1:12:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,self suddenly\Nthe barriers dissolve. One is all of
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.56,1:12:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,God.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.60,1:12:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,just as aversions come from past\Nlifetimes
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.71,1:12:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,when I heard that music I longed uh I\Ncould feel the longing
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.32,1:12:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,for that lifetime to be a vger. I didn't\Nrealize a previous lifetime I thought it
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.92,1:12:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,was a fantasy lifetime\Nto be the virgin in a great cathedral.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.19,1:12:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course when I go to Europe I go\Nfrom cathedral to cathedral.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.60,1:12:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people go from Berlin to Paris to\NLondon. I just go from St. Pat's, you
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.64,1:12:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,know, one cathedral to another. Um, so\Nthat attachment to cathedrals um to be
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.00,1:12:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of silent service to God\Nin the presence of that beauty as a form
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.15,1:12:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of worship\Nuh
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.67,1:13:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is an attachment.\NSo the karma then plays a part in our
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.15,1:13:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,ambitions,\Nour
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.52,1:13:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,daydreams,\Nour the limitation of what we think we
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.67,1:13:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,can be or accomplish in this lifetime.\NObviously people in a group like this
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.96,1:13:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,have heard uh the have responded to that\Nwhich with within them is telling them
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.56,1:13:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that the pathway to spiritual evolution\Nis theirs. So people in a room like this
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.28,1:13:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,have already evolved to an incredibly\Nadvanced degree. Advanced degree.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.28,1:13:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Advanced degree.\NWe said that only 4% of the world's
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.67,1:14:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,population ever gets over the 400s. 4%\Nlet's see gets over only only 4% get out
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.96,1:14:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,are able to transcend logic logic and\Nreason.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.76,1:14:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So although this is the crown jewel,\Nlogic and reason is the alleged crown
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.04,1:14:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,jewel of man.\NYou know,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.92,1:14:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the difference between men and animals\Nis that men can think. Yeah. Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.64,1:14:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh\Nthis is supposedly the crown jewel of
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.04,1:14:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,man from the viewpoint of education.\Num the viewpoint of the social social
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.08,1:14:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution,\Nthe capacity to think and reason
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.44,1:14:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to um be able to develop science and all\Nthe great benefits of science. So the
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.19,1:14:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,400s are enormously beneficial. Without\Nthe 400s, half of us wouldn't be in this
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.19,1:14:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,room. We would have died of\Nthings that we now cure with penicellin
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.92,1:15:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and streptoy and surgery and many other\Nthings.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.15,1:15:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So reason is the great salvation from\Nthe animal world.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.19,1:15:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So down here we're stuck in the animal\Nworld. Then we transcend into humanness
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.15,1:15:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and with the exception of kitties and\Ndogs.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.88,1:15:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We somehow passed us by. I don't know\Nhow they got up there.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.71,1:15:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We we hit willingness. See willingness\Nis different than ambition. Ambition
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.52,1:15:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,will get you through medical school.\NYou got to be a workhorse. But to be a
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.08,1:15:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,good doctor takes something else. Takes\Nwillingness will then it takes something
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.12,1:15:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,different. Willingness, acceptance,\Nand uh easygoingness and then finally an
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.00,1:15:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,unconditional compassion for human\Nsuffering.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.00,1:16:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But those are beyond reason.\NBut in a group like this, we know that
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.84,1:16:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,because of one's karmic propensity that\None is evolved up into the 400s. In the
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.32,1:16:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,400s we read, we go to lectures.\Num
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.15,1:16:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,we visit cathedrals, we begin to\Nappreciate
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.48,1:16:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is already within us the\Nhigher uh levels of consciousness and
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.00,1:16:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it's merely a matter of identifying with\Nthem.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.60,1:16:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So everyone here already has the highest\Nlevel of consciousness within them.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.67,1:16:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And the difficulty then is not the\Nfailure to acknowledge it because many
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.44,1:16:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,people in this room are quite devout\Nbut
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.56,1:16:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the habit of identifying\Nwith the mind with the ego with logic as
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.04,1:16:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who you are. So the problem then is\Nreally one of identification.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.00,1:17:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,To identify with the content rather than\Nthe context to identify with the content
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.56,1:17:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of form, logic, reason, feeling etc. And\Nto fail to realize that one is
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.84,1:17:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,context.\NKaren,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.12,1:17:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,are you there?\NLet's have that music at 7:50 again and
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.84,1:17:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,then we'll take a break. I'm going to\Nget out of those seats until I tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.60,1:17:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't give me permission.\NAnybody ever seen Neil Call Sunday
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.88,1:17:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,nights the History Channel? It's\Nhysterical. You're a vet of World War
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.40,1:17:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,II. But the lead actor in that, he comes\Non like a caricature of a a top
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.23,1:17:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,sergeant, you know, and he says, "Don't\Ntouch that channel. Nobody gave you
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.08,1:17:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,permission. I'll tell you when it's time\Nto leave this program."
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.60,1:18:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It just breaks me up because\Nit represents that anything if
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.88,1:18:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,recontextualizes\Ntotally changes its flavor and
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.32,1:18:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,significance. You see, in other words,\Nin that context, his attitude is
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.23,1:18:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,hysterically funny\Nbecause you're not victim. In another
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.36,1:18:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,circumstance, he would be terrifying.\NWhen I was 17 years old, the top bosen's
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.04,1:18:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,mate, you know, would terrify me. He'd\Nsay, "THOSE PILLOWS ARE NOT STRAIGHT
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.40,1:18:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,LINE." HOLY CHRIST, your heart was hard.\NSo, the context was different. What
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.96,1:18:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,happened to that beautiful music? I\Nwanted to hear that again.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.52,1:19:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That brings you back to the truth of\Nthat which you truly are
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.36,1:19:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and we forget\Nyou
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.44,1:19:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,reality.\Nhave you all here today as a blessing.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.76,1:19:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be back in half hour.\NHalleluah.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.80,1:20:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Halle\NHalleluah.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.12,1:20:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Halleluah.\NHalleluah.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.36,1:20:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Hallelu\NHallelujah.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.12,1:20:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So that which is God and that which is\Nbeauty are one thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.08,1:20:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't like to talk about halfway\Nthrough the heart
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.67,1:21:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> because it's doesn't last long.\N>> Adoration, devotional, worship.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.00,1:21:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone asked, "How do you get beyond\N>> the thinkingness of the mind?"
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.88,1:21:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And beauty is one of the most immediate\Nones.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.44,1:21:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Beauty of the music takes you out of\Nthinking this in one instant.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.48,1:21:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Halleluah.\N>> It's like incredible beauty immobilizes
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.08,1:22:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind.\NSo beauty then is
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.48,1:22:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the awareness\Nof the grace of God
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.36,1:22:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,which is different than\Ndiscussing the various things we disced.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.36,1:22:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,does\Nit's the um way around the mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.56,1:22:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody asked how do you how do you\Nstop that thinking?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.04,1:22:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You become enamored of God instead of\Nenamored of the thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.28,1:23:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,To discern the presence of God and all\Nthat exists
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.19,1:23:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is a gift that suddenly comes forth of\Nits own
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.00,1:23:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,when\Nthe willingness to surrender all that
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.04,1:23:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,stands in its way.\NThe gratification, the satisfaction, the
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.80,1:23:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,excitement of thinking this,\Nfeeling this, emotions.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.63,1:23:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great leap because\Nwe transcend
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.84,1:23:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the\Ninstincts of the animal. We transcend
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.04,1:23:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the thinkingness of\Nhomo sapien
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.92,1:24:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and respond to the divinity within us.\NWe said this morning
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.28,1:24:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and verified it.\NOut of the unmanifest arises the
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.28,1:24:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,manifest.\NOut of the manifest arises existence as
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.00,1:24:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,beingness.\NAnd with that existence arises
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.76,1:24:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness\Nand the energy of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.04,1:24:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, all that has life arises from\Nthe unmanifest to the manifest through
Dialogue: 0,1:24:27.36,1:24:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,existence and beingness through\Nconsciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.80,1:24:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and awareness.\NAll that is created by God has within it
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.04,1:24:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,divinity.\NLet's see if that's so
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.23,1:24:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,all that exists has within it this its\Nsource as divinity resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.76,1:25:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, then the awareness of the\Npresence of God as a source of one's own
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.80,1:25:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,existence is innate\Nwithin consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.44,1:25:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It is already present\Nand it's only a matter of
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.36,1:25:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,letting go the identifications with all\Nthat stand in its way.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.96,1:25:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The purposes of the lectures\Nprior to last month were to
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.44,1:25:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,by familiarity and by description and by\Nanalysis
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.60,1:25:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,understand the structure of the ego\Nand by understanding it have the
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.63,1:25:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,capacity to disassemble it.\NAnd we always start the lectures
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.92,1:26:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,by reminding ourselves\Nthat all that is is what it is by virtue
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.63,1:26:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,of the divinity of its creation. Each\Nthing is only becoming manifesting its
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.44,1:26:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you might say karmic propensity to be\Nthat which it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.52,1:26:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, there's no reason to worry\Nabout God
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.36,1:26:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,or reaching God or being with God or\Nanything because one is constantly in
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.67,1:26:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the presence of God\Nwho is the source of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.71,1:26:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which arises you're worrying\Nabout God.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.84,1:26:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need to worry about God.\NThere's only the capacity to appreciate
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.04,1:26:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,beauty.\NThe the exquisite power of
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.52,1:27:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,perfection. So beauty rep is\Na style of recognizing the perfection of
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.19,1:27:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,all that exists.\NAs spiritual awareness progresses, the
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.88,1:27:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,awareness of the perfection and\Nintrinsic beauty of all that exists
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.44,1:27:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes overwhelming.\NAnd at a certain point, it becomes
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.12,1:27:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,incapacitating.\NAnd if the music is beautiful enough,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.60,1:27:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't stand up and talk. You have to\Nsit down.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.08,1:27:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether the body eats or doesn't eat,\Nyou can see how quickly all that becomes
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.28,1:27:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,irrelevant.\NYou go into a state of spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.71,1:27:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,ecstasy.\NThe survival of the physicality depends
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.28,1:27:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,on your neighbors.\NIf you have friendly neighbors that drop
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.67,1:28:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in, the body survives. If not, it\Ndoesn't. And it's totally immaterial.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.80,1:28:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody says it's time to eat now and\Nso you eat otherwise you'll completely
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.76,1:28:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,forget all about it.\NSo as we get into the higher levels of
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.60,1:28:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the 500s, you know,\Nyou get into a benevolence towards life,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.08,1:28:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,a benevolence towards yourself,\Nbenevolence to all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.60,1:28:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a benevolence towards\Neven the most horrific
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.52,1:28:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,because it cannot help itself but be\Nwhat it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.08,1:28:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have the karmic\Nwhatever it takes to not be other than
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.40,1:28:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that which it is.\NAnd then in a greater level,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.48,1:29:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,one says there's no reason for it to be\Nother than what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.08,1:29:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It can just be what it is.\NNot particularly saintly,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.00,1:29:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but so it is what it is.\NAnd there's letting go, wanting to
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.32,1:29:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,change anything as it is. Because you\Nsee, the only thing you want to change
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.32,1:29:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is your perception of it all and your\Njudgmentalism about it. You want bin
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.44,1:29:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Laden to be different than what he is.\NNo, I don't want Bin Laden to be
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.08,1:29:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,different than what he is. Then who\Nwould be bin Laden?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.84,1:29:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody's got to be the bad example of\Nthe day. You know,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.92,1:29:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,getting their Muslim all gone here, you\Nknow, all the bad guys of when I was
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.40,1:29:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,young,\Nnew guys arise on the stage.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.08,1:30:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the highest dimension, one sees\Nthat that is all
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.36,1:30:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,like a hologram.\NAnd there's no point to change the
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.28,1:30:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,hologram because it's evolving out of\Nits own intrinsic innate
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.56,1:30:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,perfect balance and order within itself.\NAll is merely becoming that which it is
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.63,1:30:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,in its expression within physicality.\NThere's no need to change anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.04,1:30:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We become our potential. Not because\Nit's going to do something for the
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.04,1:30:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,world, not because it's going to do\Nsomething for us.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.52,1:30:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are kindly thoughts.\NKindly thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.36,1:31:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But in actuality the overall\Nconsciousness field of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.88,1:31:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is\Nelevating is going developing because of
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.28,1:31:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,who we are.\NThe only thing you need to do the better
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.96,1:31:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the life of all mankind\Nis to appreciate the beauty of that
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.76,1:31:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,incredible music.\NYou've done all you can do to
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.19,1:31:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,acknowledge the presence of God, to feel\Nthe exquisite joy of that beauty.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.76,1:31:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Sends out a vibration\Nof such immense power.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.23,1:31:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, because power cannot be\Nresisted whereas force can.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.52,1:31:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That power of your adoration of God,\Nyour love, your devotion
Dialogue: 0,1:31:50.56,1:31:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,radiates out and elevates the whole\Nfield of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.23,1:32:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and it affects millions of people who\Nare even not even aware they're being
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.80,1:32:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,afflicted.\NJust as the person is about to do this
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.00,1:32:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,something, he says he lets it go. He\Ndoesn't know why he let it go.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.67,1:32:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because the field is so high now it\Nmakes that kind of an action almost
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.28,1:32:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,impossible.\NSo what we do then
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.12,1:32:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is by the realization of our own innate\Nperfection
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.48,1:32:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in impact the consciousness of all of\Nmankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.92,1:32:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,re reccalibrated u the level of\Nconsciousness as it
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.40,1:32:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,has moved forward over the centuries\Nin the late 1980s. That was the time of
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.48,1:32:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the harmonic conversions.\NThat was the time when all the spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.44,1:32:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,committed people in the world joined\Ntogether at a certain hour in the
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.40,1:33:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,morning. We all woke up at 4:00 or\Nsomething and prayed for peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.92,1:33:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the time when monolithic\Natheistic communism
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.60,1:33:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,collapsed.\NAll of those things. And I suppose there
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.32,1:33:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,was some kind of a confluence\Nastrologically.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:15.60,1:33:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Not because the astrologic formation\Ncauses things, but because that which
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.88,1:33:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,brings peace brings\Nsimultaneously many things all at the
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.76,1:33:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,same time that are in concordance with\Neach other. Huh.
